Swiss Raiffeisen CEO Backs Sarasin-Vontobel Merger, SZ Reports

-- B y   C o r i n n e   G r e t l e r
-- 
2011-10-16T09:17:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-16/swiss-raiffeisen-ceo-backs-sarasin-vontobel-merger-sz-reports.html
Swiss Raiffeisen group Chief
Executive Officer Pierin Vincenz favors a longer-term merger of
Sarasin Bank & Cie. AG with Vontobel Holding AG,  SonntagsZeitung 
reported, citing an unidentified person.  Raiffeisen acquired 12.5 percent of Vontobel in 2004 and
Vincenz is a member of its board, the newspaper added.  Sarasin, Raiffeisen and Rabobank Groep NV have been in
talks in the past two weeks over a agreement under which
Raiffeisen would acquire 33 percent of Rabobankâ€™s voting shares
